result.name: ZAKKA

reviews.text:
Nice place to have lunch, the quantity served was generous and the price was cheap for this location. Food was good, not the best one but still good taste. They use a nice combination of ingredients that makes the dishes different. 

It’s a half served place, you pay first in the cashier area. They still will serve the plates to your table. For napkins, sauces, extra plates and cups you have to take them from a counter yourself.

It's very underwhelming.
The food was very mild and the staff were very unenthusiastic, they took a while to serve one of our orders and no apologies were given when informed.

It's a convenient lunch place. Their dishes are delicious fusion style. Staff humble and comfy seats.
I sometimes whish they had more healthy choices on the menu.
Very tasty food and relaxing casual environment! Very nice fluffy soufflé pancakes too!
Delightful experience with reasonable cost.
